feel free to help out with the merchants’ requests here.

We’ve cleared the ruins and debris from the shopping street.
\n<Armor Shop Merchant>Residents have started gathering in the southern area to rebuild their lives.
\n<Armor Shop Merchant>Mr. Yamashita and the others seem to be working on something at the factory up north...
We’ve been instructed to remain on the southern side as much as possible.
\n<Armor Shop Merchant>As you can see, the shopping street is still under reconstruction.
\n<Armor Store Merchant>There’s a new task for you. Go speak with the chairman of our shopping street association.
Actually, it’s just Mr. Sakamoto from the gun shop.
He’s always looked out for us merchants, both before and after the disaster.
\n<Armor Shop Merchant>He should be near the hotel on the southwest side.
\n<Armorsmith>There’s a new task for you. Go speak with the chairman of our shopping street association.

He’s always looked out for us merchants, both before and after the disaster.
\n<Armor Shop Merchant>He should be near the hotel on the southwest side.
\n<Worker> There are still plenty of surplus supplies in the shopping district
\n<Worker> Now we need to bring them back to the safe zone for unified management.
The door is tightly closed... I wonder if there are any survivors inside.
He doesn't seem to have anything to say.
\n<Worker>The residents and shopkeepers of the shopping street are now all gathered staying at the inn below.
Living together makes life more convenient.
<Worker> The things in this convenience store have all been scavenged by the Wild Dogs Gang.

Do you want to go to the forest to gather building materials?

It's better not to go out of the safe zone at night...
\n<Worker> Is there really any point in repairing this warehouse...?
How about helping to build the merchant stalls instead?
\N<Guard>Hey, young man. The survivors in our apartment building have cleaned things up a bit.
Let’s stick together and stay in this hotel for now.
\N<Guard>That said, this area’s still off-limits to others. Sorry about that.
\N<Guard>I heard you’ve been helping the local merchants gather supplies.
\n<Sakamoto>Anyway, to get to the point—the shopping district is almost fully repaired.
The merchants are just too scared to open up for business.
\n<Sakamoto>So, what do they do? Build a bunch of useless fences.
Guess that gives these wimps a bit of peace of mind.
\n<Sakamoto>You want them to reopen too, right?
\n<Sakamoto>I’ll throw in a real weapon as your reward.
\n<Sakamoto>Fixing those damn fences will probably take 15 building materials.
\n<Sakamoto>Come back and let me know once you’ve gathered everything.
\n<Sakamoto>Also, looks like a zombie wandered in from the woods over there.
Not the strongest, but definitely a pain to deal with.
\n<Sakamoto>Why not clear them out while you’re at it?
one person draws the zombies’ attention,
Only brings up the biggest headaches after I’ve already taken the mission...
You’re something else—I really underestimated you.
Next time you come by the shopping street,
they should have that fence fixed.
\..\..The merchants will likely be open for business too.
\n<Sakamoto>Drop by my shop then, and I’ll have your reward ready.
\n<Sakamoto>Not enough materials. Don’t try to pull a fast one on me.
\n<Sakamoto>No need to rush. Come back tomorrow.
\n<Sakamoto>The supplies will be ready by then.
